channel.title: An RS2 item id list
channel.description:
so i was reading on www.powerbot.org that i could find 1 here. i did a search and found a link, but im not sure if its just a Pserver custom Id list or the actually runescape.com list. seems weird to me that the list would start out like this
0 - Dwarf remains 1 - Toolkit 2 - Cannonball 3 - Nulodion's notes 4 - Ammo mould 5 - Instruction manual 6 - Cannon base 799 - Not Existing 7 - Cannon base 8 - Cannon stand 9 - Cannon stand 10 - Cannon barrels 11 - Cannon barrels 12 - Cannon furnace 13 - Cannon furnace 14 - Railing 15 - Holy table napkin
im sort of assuming it would be like RSC with the first 1k or so Item ID's
so can anyone help me out here?

item.title: An RS2 item id list
item.dc:creator: @GLeU GLeU
item.description:
@GLeU wrote:

[quote author=flj0yter0p link=topic=460202.msg3367153#msg3367153 date=1286881507]
I think the ids you have on private servers are the same as runescape because people dump item ids from the clients.

nah i compared some and they were different.

[quote=“RuneSpace, post:1, topic:363988”]You can get ids from runescape.com

Go into g.e database and find an item

then view page source then Ctrl+F

Paste this in

http://services.runescape.com/m=itemdb_rs/3128_obj_big.gif?id=

IT will show something like

http://services.runescape.com/m=itemdb_rs/3128_obj_big.gif?id=11218[/quote]

hey thanks alot dude. that helps quite a bit.
